fields.title: Share has been so good!
fields.author: Anonymous
fields.content:
My work explores the relationship between multiculturalism and vegetarian ethics.

 

With influences as diverse as Caravaggio and Andy Warhol, new variations are generated from both traditional and modern narratives.

Ever since I was a child I have been fascinated by the theoretical limits of the human condition.

fields.title: Share is Great!
fields.author: Anonymous
fields.content:
What starts out as yearning soon becomes corrupted into a cacophony of greed, leaving only a sense of decadence and the chance of a new reality.

As shifting derivatives become distorted through studious and diverse practice, the viewer is left with a hymn to the inaccuracies of our condition.

fields.header: Do you have a disabled child? (aged 3-19 years)
fields.content: As a registered charity we have been supporting families since 1982. We offer a wide range of opportunities for young people with disabilities . We do this through our holiday and out of school clubs with a range of fun activities within a happy safe and relaxed environment. We have a high staff ratio and are all highly qualified and CRB checked.

We’ve created activities that are fun, smart, and save the day when school is out. We have preschool and school-age programs that kids love. We offer flexible scheduling options to meet the needs of busy families like yours.

Every child is different, but they all have one thing in common. They like to have fun! That’s why we’ve designed many different programs for summertime that are safe, conveniently located and flexible enough to work with your busy schedule.

As a registered charity we have been supporting families since 1982. Not only will your child have a chance to be part of something they are already interested in but they’ll have a chance to discover something brand new.

• Arts & Crafts!
  • A fantastic garden with bikes and toys!
  • Soft play and sensory room!
  • Playsation, Nitendo Wii & Computers!
  • Face Painting!

fields.info:
We offer a range of opportunities for young people with additional need, within our provision we offer different sessions from preschool to school age which include:

        Cooking

            Art & crafts

                Music

                      Table tennis

                               Gardening

                                      Wii / Xbox

 

Children benefit by learning social skills with workers who take the  time and opportunity to teach new skills whilst making new friends.

 

For parents we provide a sense of care and well-being for their children, giving peace of mind and respite.

 

We have a range of highly qualified staff.  

 

All our staff get to know the children's needs so as to understand the importance of individuality.  

 

Staff will care for each individual child accordingly.

 

We run the following clubs:

             After School 

Tuesdays & Thursday 3pm - 7pm

            Saturday - 10-3pm 

Holiday clubs run throughout the year - 10-3pm

 

 

Contact us for more information.
